In [18]:
def get_crystal_coincidence(vol_types, geom):
    hit_and_left = np.logical_and(vol_types, vol_types[geom.shift_wires(1)])
    hit_and_right = np.logical_and(vol_types, vol_types[geom.shift_wires(-1)])
    return np.logical_or(hit_and_left, hit_and_right)
In [29]:
def get_trigger_signal(vol_types, geom):
    print np.nonzero(vol_types)
    # Get the crystals with neighbouring hits
    trig_crys = get_crystal_coincidence(vol_types, geom)
    print np.nonzero(trig_crys)
    # Get the locations to the left and right of the cherenkov counter pairs
    # This also grabs the cherenkov pairs themselves
    lft_of_pair = trig_crys[geom.shift_wires(1)][geom.cher_crys]
    rgt_of_pair = trig_crys[geom.shift_wires(-1)][geom.cher_crys]
    trig_crys[geom.cher_crys] = np.logical_or(lft_of_pair, rgt_of_pair)
    # Get the moudle coincidence
    trig_crys[geom.up_cher] = np.logical_and(trig_crys[geom.up_scin],
                                             trig_crys[geom.up_cher])
    trig_crys[geom.down_cher] = np.logical_and(trig_crys[geom.down_scin],
                                               trig_crys[geom.down_cher])
    print np.nonzero(trig_crys)
    print np.nonzero(np.logical_and(trig_crys, vol_types))
    return np.logical_and(trig_crys, vol_types)
